As a white guy I don't exactly have the best basis for whether or not this is truly "authentic" but as far as I can tell this is LEGIT. This is the kind of food one would expect from a food truck in Williamsburg (but less costly!). I got queso flautas, a spicy pork taco and a goat taco. Savor those last words like I savored the food: GOAT TACO. The meat was perfect, doused with cilantro and more, in a double-shell soft taco. The spicy pork did not disappoint and the flautas were nice, crispy, and cheesy (and covered with more crumbly cheese and lettuce). This food was *exactly* what I was craving - - I'm glad I took the detour from my destination to find something other than the big chain fast food places in the neighborhood, and I was certainly not disappointed.
